Totally, I get what you're saying. Maybe "private block" would be the best terminology here, whereas a cross-client "mute" could be done with a Scuttlebot plugin (and `addMap()`):

```js
sbot.addMap((val, cb) => {
  if (val.value.author = target) {
    val.value.content = {}
  }

  cb(null, val)
})
```

